{"name": "mkx", "metadata": {"name": "mkx", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "Intended Audience :: System Administrators", "Intended Audience :: Telecommunications Industry", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Natural Language :: English", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Topic :: Internet", "Topic :: Security"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["typer", "pydantic", "pysnmp", "requests"], "summary": "Tool for auditing Mikrotik routers, searching for vulnerabilities and information about the target device.", "upload_time": 1733494189}, "documentation": ["# MKX - Mikrotik Exploit\n\nMKX is a tool for auditing Mikrotik routers, searching for vulnerabilities and information about the target device.\n\n## Features\n\n### Obtaining Information\n\n- Discovery of other Mikrotik devices on the local network through the MikroTik Neighbor Discovery protocol (MNDP) that runs on port 5678 UDP.\n- Obtaining information from a specific Mikrotik device using the SNMP protocol.\n\n### Attacks\n\n- PoC of [CVE-2018-14847](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2018-14847) that allows obtaining user credentials in vulnerable versions of RouterOS.\n- DDoS attack by sending packets to all ports randomly or to a specific port.\n- Attack that crashes the web interface of RouterOS versions 6 > 6.49.10 - [CVE-2023-30800](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-30800).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mkx.attacks.exploit", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mkx.attacks.exploit.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "ip_address", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Argument(help='Target IP address.')", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "port", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Argument(help='Winbox TCP port.')", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "mkx.attacks.exploit.command", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mkx.attacks.ddos", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mkx.attacks.ddos.http", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "target", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Argument(help='Target IP address or domain.')", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "port", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Argument(help='TCP port to be attacked.')", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "random", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Option(\n            '--random', '-r', help='Attacks random ports between 1 and 65534.'\n        )", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Option('--verbose', '-v', help='Enable verbosity.')", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "mkx.attacks.ddos.RESET", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.attacks.ddos.BOLD", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.attacks.ddos.RED", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.attacks.ddos.YELLOW", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.attacks.ddos.GREEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.attacks.ddos.command", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mkx.attacks.kill_web_server", "documentation": ["CVE-2023-30800", "The web server used by MikroTik RouterOS version 6 is affected", "by a heap memory corruption issue. A remote and unauthenticated", "attacker can corrupt the server's heap memory by sending a", "crafted HTTP request. As a result, the web interface crashes and", "is immediately restarted. The issue was fixed in RouterOS 6.49.10 stable.", "RouterOS version 7 is not affected.", "More information at: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-30800"], "functions": [{"name": "mkx.attacks.kill_web_server.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "target", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Argument(\n            help='Target IP address or list of IP addresses and TCP ports.'\n        )", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "https", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Option(\n            '--https', '-s', help='Configure the attack for an https server.'\n        )", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Attack that crashes the web interface of RouterOS versions 6 > 6.49.10.\n\nCVE-2023-30800\n\nThe web server used by MikroTik RouterOS version 6 is affected by\na heap memory corruption issue. A remote and unauthenticated attacker\ncan corrupt the server's heap memory by sending a crafted HTTP request.\nAs a result, the web interface crashes and is immediately restarted.\nThe issue was fixed in RouterOS 6.49.10 stable.\nRouterOS version 7 is not affected.\n\n**Examples:**\n\n- mkx kill-web-server 172.16.0.123:80\n\n- mkx kill-web-server 172.16.0.123:80,172.16.0.124:80"]}], "variables": [{"name": "mkx.attacks.kill_web_server.DATA", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.attacks.kill_web_server.command", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mkx", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mkx.discovery.mac_server_discover", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mkx.discovery.mac_server_discover.discovery", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sock_discovery", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.discovery.mac_server_discover.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "table", "type": {"name": "Annotated", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Annotated", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "typer.Option(\n            '--table', '-t', help='Prints a table with the search results.'\n        )", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "mkx.discovery.mac_server_discover.MAC_START", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.discovery.mac_server_discover.IDENTITY_START", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.discovery.mac_server_discover.IDENTITY_END", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mkx.disco